                     <summary/>
                     <msItem xml:id="p1_i1">
                        <locus from="2ra" to="286rb"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1586Hayman">Hāymānota ʾabaw</title>
                        <note>Table of contents is provided on <locus from="285rb" to="286rb"/></note>
                        <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                           <locus target="#286vab"/><foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈጸመ፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሃይማኖት፡
                              ዘይነግር፡ ተዋሕዶተ፡ መለኮት <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/>፨ ወፍጻሜሁኒ፡ ኮነ፡ በ፷፻ወ፮፻፡ ፵ወ፮፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም፡ በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡
                           በ፪፻፷ወ፪፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፨ እንዘ፡ አብቅቴ፡ ወርኀ፡ ፬፡ በ፳ወ፮፡ መጥቅዕ፨ ወእንዘ፡ አብቅቴ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ፯፨ እንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡
                           ፀሐይ፡ በሳድስ፡ ኆኅቱ፨ እም፡ ሐምስ፡ ኆኅት፡ በጊዜ፡ ግብአቱ፨ በ፫ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ <del rend="erasure"/>፡ በጸጋ፡
                           እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘተሰምየ፡ ሥልጣን፡ ሰገድ፡ ወጳጳስሂ፡ አሜሃ፡ አቡነ፡ ስምዖን፨ ወካዕበ፡ ኮነ፡ ፍጻሜሁኒ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡
                           ሃይማኖት፡ አመ፡ ፭፡ ዘወርኃ፡ ጵዮን፨ በነገረ፡ ሱርስት፨ ወሮሜሂ፡ ሚጥርዮስ፨ ወበዕብራይስጥ፤ ሐዚራን፨ ወበግዕዝሂ፡ ሰኔ፨
                           ወዘአጽሐፎ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አባ፡ ዘክርስቶስ፡ መምህረ፡ ሕግ፡ ወሥርዓት፨ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ ተዝካረ፡ በምድር፡ ወበሰማያት፨
                           ወዘጸሐፎሂ፡ ወልዱ፡ መልክዐ፡ ክርስቶስ፨ እግዚአብሔር፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ኢየሩሳሌም፡ ሰማያዊ፨ ምስለ፡ ሱታፌሁ፡ ጽጌ፡
                           ሐይማኖት፨ ወፈድፋደሰ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ዘክርስቶስ፡ ዘጻመወ፡ ለአጽሕፎ፡ በጥብዓተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፨ ኢትርሥዕዎ፡ ወትረ፡ ኵልክሙ፡
                           ደቂቀ፡ ዳሞ፡ ዐቢይ፡ ወንኡስ፨ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፨</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="en">This ‘Book of the Faith’, which talks about the union of divinity, was completed
                              with the help of God <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/>. And its completion happened in <date calendar="world" when-custom="6646" when="1154">6646  year of the world,</date>
                              in the year of Mark the Evangelist, in <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="262" when="1610">262 year of mercy.</date> When the <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabqǝte</foreign> of the
                              month was 4 and the <foreign xml:lang="gez">maṭqǝʿ</foreign> was 26. And when the <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabqǝte</foreign> of the sun was 7; when the sun was at the 6th height; from the 5th height at the time of its rise. 
                              In the <date when="1610">3rd year</date> of reign of our King <del rend="erasure"/> by the grace of God who was called
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos">Śǝlṭān Sagad</persName> and Metropolitan ʾAbuna <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8740Semon">Sǝmʿon</persName>. 
                              And again the completion of this ‘Book of the Faith’ happened on the 5th of the month <foreign xml:lang="syr">Ṗǝyon</foreign> in the Syriac
                              speech and in Roman <foreign xml:lang="la">Miṭrǝyos</foreign> and in Hebrew <foreign xml:lang="he">Hazirān</foreign> and in Gǝʿǝz <foreign xml:lang="gez">Sane</foreign>. 
                              And the one who commissioned this book was ʾAbbā <persName role="patron" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14617Zakrestos">Zakrǝstos</persName>, the teacher of law and
                              order, so that it might become memorial in earth and in heaven. And the one who
                              wrote it was his son <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14616MalkeaKrestos">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos</persName>. May God write their names in Heavenly
                              Jerusalem; together with associate <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14717SegeHaymanot">Ṣǝge Hāymānot</persName>; and particularly for
                              ʾAbuna <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14617Zakrestos">Zakrǝstos</persName> who took the trouble to commission it in perseverance of flesh and soul.
                              May thou never forget all the children of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">Dāmmo</placeName>, the great and the minor. Forever and ever, Amen. </foreign>
                           <note>The colophon mentions the regnal name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">King</t:roleName> Śǝlṭān Sagad I</persName>
                              (the King’s ‘worldly’ name, Susǝnyos, is erased) as well as the names of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8740Semon"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="function">Metropolitan</t:roleName> <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="function">ʾAbuna</t:roleName>  Sǝmʿon</persName> (in tenure <date>1607–1617</date>), 
                              the commissioner <persName role="patron" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14617Zakrestos"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">ʾAbbā</t:roleName> Zakrǝstos</persName>, <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14616MalkeaKrestos">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos</persName> 
                              and his companion <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14717SegeHaymanot">Ṣǝge Hāymānot</persName>.
                              For the completion of the manuscript the dates mentioned are <date calendar="world" when-custom="6646" when="1154">6646 year of the
                                 world</date>, <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="262" when="1610">262 year of mercy</date> and the <date when="1610">3rd year</date> of the reign of
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName>, i.e., Śǝlṭān Sagad, that is in 1610 CE. There is a discrepancy between the year of the world, which gives 1154 CE, on the one hand, and the year of mercy and the 3rd year of the reign 
                              of Susǝnyos, that is 1610, on the other. The <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabqǝtes</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">maṭqǝʿ</foreign> correspond to the year 1610. Most probably 6646 year of the world is a mistake.</note>
                        </colophon>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
               
